verbose_text: This is in line with reports showing that Ag catalysts are in principle more active than Au in H 2 dissociation,20 which is often the rate limiting step in hydrogenation reactions for Au.31 The lower activity of Ag catalyst, despite its low activation energy, can be ascribed to the pre-exponential factor in the Arrhenius model, which is three orders of magnitude lower than that for Au.
